social_posts.post_text: Because what's worse than pacing back and forth during THE test all day? Pacing back and forth during THE test all day with nothing to look at.

Wrapping up the year with Genius Hour projects, so we ditched the sticky notes and started with brain writing on Miro! Today was my first time ever using it, and there seems like so much more we can do…for next year let’s calm down. 😆 They wrote their top 3 topic ideas on the first row, and then we did five rounds of sharing ways they can explore their topics further. The end result generated 110 total ideas within this class alone. 👏🏼👏🏼👏🏼

Just moved my entire classroom dorm FB marketplace furnished apartment into a closet in my new room, and I’m off to summer! I have ideas for those giant windows and propagating plants. That’s about all I’ll let my brain consider for next year’s new grade level. ✌🏼🤍☀️
#teachersonsummerbreak

This is a VERY niche post, but if you've been here a while you know that @texaslonestarteacher is my person! The world is a small place, like that time when I was a junior and she was a freshman at the same high school circa 2002/2003. Now looks at us. Who would've thought. Not me!
This might be my most favorite room yet, and I had to share some of of the pieces and spots coming together. Feels so light, open, and cozy! 🤍🌿

POV: You get a dopamine boost every time the sticky note drawer is opened to use on the Status of the Class Chart. It’s not solely because of the sticky note colors! It’s because you’ve given power to your people to stay on it with their tasks and you’ve streamlined this between your two classes with your teammate, @theamygroesbeck! 

Grab this one in her TPT shop plus all the extras she added in there! Linked in my profile too.

READING IS THE REWARD. THE REWARD IS READING!
My third graders have been asking what the beads are for each day! 👏🏼 It’s a book tracker! My teammate introduced me to it in 5th with the 40 book challenge. I’m keeping it very simple this year. Students read, creatively reflect on their book (could be a social media post from the main character, could be the villain’s soundtrack to their life, etc.), we have ourselves a book talk, and they earn a bead to add to their tracker. At the end of the year they take it home as a gift. It makes my 90’s heart so happy too. 🤩

Prepped and ready for our reward system! Raffle tickets go into the repurposed q-tip holders, I draw on Friday, and we celebrate! So far stickers and kinder buddy tutoring passes are the most popular! PLUS, they get to visit their former kinder teachers from their year of virtual learning. This was also the most requested when I taught 5th. 🤍
